  "id": "",
  "summary": "nolimit-x ships heavily obfuscated code in hidden.ad/ directory",
  "details": "The package contains 45 JavaScript files under a hidden `.ad/` directory (from-generator.js, phone-validator.js, sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, web-command.js, x0.js through xz.js) that are heavily obfuscated using hex-identifier mangling (e.g., `_0x47a0b3`, `_0x476120`). File names suggest SMS/SMTP/phone-validation tooling — a category historically associated with abuse (bulk-SMS, bypass, spam infrastructure) — and the use of a dot-prefixed `.ad/` directory hides the contents from casual `ls` inspection. The behavior of the obfuscated bundles was not traced end-to-end, so it cannot be confirmed whether installing or requiring the package executes them automatically or whether they perform exfiltration, RCE, or credential harvesting. The combined signals (bulk obfuscated code, hidden directory, suggestive file names) warrant human review before allowing this version into a build pipeline.",
